_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\ntests/src/org.springframework/spring-jcl/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_jcl/LogAdapterTest.java:16:    private static final String LOGGER_NAME = \"spring-jcl.dynamic-access\";\ntests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org_jboss_logmanager/jboss_logmanager/Formatters12Test.java:51:                \"Anonymous privileged-action construction is only needed for JVM dynamic-access coverage